# Cloudflare Pages redirects
# Syntax: <from> <to> <status>  (200=rewrite, 301=permanent, 302=temp)
# See https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/

# Canonical trailing-slash for docs
/docs  /docs/  301

# Legacy /getting-started.html → mkdocs Material doc (Wave 23 cleanup).
# Real onboarding lives at /docs/getting-started/. Internal links across
# site/index.html, prescreen-demo.js, etc. still point at the .html path;
# this server-side 301 is the primary fallback. site/getting-started.html
# also exists as a meta-refresh stub for Cloudflare's static-first path.
/getting-started.html  /docs/getting-started/  301
/getting-started       /docs/getting-started/  301

# NOTE: removed legacy `/programs/UNI-:id → /programs/ 301`. Per-program
# SEO pages now live at /programs/UNI-xxx.html (10,951 deployed). CF Pages
# auto-strips .html. If a legacy non-existent UNI-* path is hit, 404.

# NOTE: pretty URL rewrites removed — CF Pages auto-strips .html
# extension, so /pricing → site/pricing.html works natively. The
# explicit `/pricing → /pricing.html 200` rules caused an infinite
# redirect loop because CF Pages re-rewrote /pricing.html → /pricing.

# Device flow activation — RFC 8628 verification_uri.
# /go/ABCD-1234 → /go (page reads code from URL path or ?code= query).
# Bare /go works natively via CF .html stripping.
# S3 friction-removal landing — /go/upgrade?from=429 (linked from anon
# 429 body + X-Anon-Upgrade-Url header) is the anon → paid conversion
# entry point. Redirected to /go so users land on the existing Stripe
# checkout UI without forking the device-flow logic; ?from=429 is
# preserved by the 302 for funnel attribution.
/go/upgrade /go  302
/go/:code /go  302

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Common-broken inbound paths — catch-all redirects so external links from
# blog posts, social media, CMS imports, and "guess-the-URL" attempts land
# on a real page instead of 404. All targets verified to exist on disk.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# /blog → published mkdocs blog under docs.
# We intentionally do not host a /blog landing page; the launch-week posts
# and ongoing release notes live at /docs/blog/. site/blog/*.md are source
# files only (not served as pages).
/blog        /docs/blog/  301
/blog/*      /docs/blog/  301

# /api → REST API reference. Common guess from people who heard "API"
# before finding the docs index. /docs/api-reference/ is the canonical home.
/api         /docs/api-reference/  301
/api/*       /docs/api-reference/  301

# Auth-style aliases — we have no separate sign-in page; account / API key
# management lives on the dashboard, which uses device-flow login.
/sign-in     /dashboard.html  302
/signin      /dashboard.html  302
/login       /dashboard.html  302
/log-in      /dashboard.html  302
/signup      /dashboard.html  302
/sign-up     /dashboard.html  302
/register    /dashboard.html  302

# Contact — there is no dedicated contact page; info@bookyou.net is the
# operator inbox and /go.html is the only first-party interaction surface.
/contact     /go.html  302
/contact-us  /go.html  302
/support     /go.html  302

# Legacy "jpintel" brand — the product was renamed to AutonoMath
# (jpintel collides with Intel as a 著名商標). Anything pointing at the old
# brand should land on the homepage. Internal source path src/jpintel_mcp/
# is unaffected; this is user-facing only.
/jpintel        /  301
/jpintel.html   /  301
/jpintel/*      /  301

# Dashboard convenience — bare /dashboard works via CF .html stripping,
# but /dash and /account are common shortcuts users try.
/dash        /dashboard.html  302
/account     /dashboard.html  302
